title: Glastonbury 2016 - Mystery Jets
description:
Glastonbury 2016: Mystery Jets

Transformed into the otherworldly genre of space rock, Mystery Jets have Glasto in awe.




Set List on John Peel Stage on 26 Jun 2016 at Worthy Farm, Pilton:-

Telomere
Serotonin
Flash a Hungry Smile
Midnight's Mirror
Blood Red Balloon
Half In Love With Elizabeth
Bombay Blue
Bubblegum
Young Love (feat. Laura Marling)
Two Doors Down
Alice Springs



Mystery Jets Biography

Mystery Jets are an English indie rock band, formerly based on Eel Pie Island in Twickenham, London. The band was formed by Henry Harrison (lyrics, piano), Blaine Harrison (vocals, guitar and keyboards) and William Rees (guitar, vocals) when the boys were still at school and would send each other songs on cassettes. The other member is Kapil Trivedi (drums).
